doc_prompt = (
    "Please convert the following technical troubleshooting content into **Confluence Storage Format (HTML/XML)**, "
    "suitable for direct use in the Confluence REST API under `representation: storage`.\n\n"
    "Follow these **strict formatting rules**:\n"
    "1. **Headings:** Use `<h2>` for top-level sections (e.g., 'Check Instance Status'), and `<h3>` for sub-sections.\n"
    "2. **Bulleted Lists:** Use `<ul><li>` for bullet points. Nest sub-bullets correctly using nested `<ul><li>` blocks.\n"
    "3. **Bold Text:** Use `<strong>your bold text</strong>`.\n"
    "4. **Code Blocks:** Wrap full code sections in the Confluence code macro format:\n"
    "   ```xml\n"
    "   <ac:structured-macro ac:name=\"code\">\n"
    "     <ac:parameter ac:name=\"language\">bash</ac:parameter>\n"
    "     <ac:plain-text-body><![CDATA[\n"
    "     # code goes here\n"
    "     ]]></ac:plain-text-body>\n"
    "   </ac:structured-macro>\n"
    "   ```\n"
    "   Make sure CDATA is correctly opened and closed and that all XML tags are well-formed.\n"
    "5. **Inline Code:** Use `<code>example_command</code>`.\n"
    "6. **Links:** Use `<a href=\"https://example.com\">link text</a>`.\n"
    "7. **Content Preservation:** Do **not** skip, summarize, or alter any words. Output must preserve **every word** from the original.\n"
    "8. **No Outer HTML Tags:** Do **not** include `<html>`, `<body>`, or `<head>` tags.\n"
    "9. **No Explanations or Comments:** Return only the cleaned and valid storage-format content block. Do not add commentary, headers, markdown, or YAML.\n\n"
    "Format the following content accordingly:\n"
    "---\n"
    f"{doc_input}\n"
    "---"
)
